08273nam a22010695i 9783110678628DE-B159720230228015514.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230228t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831106786287 a10.1515/97831106786282doi  a(DE-B1597)536688  a(OCoLC)1350386388  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aHD585b.L58 202304a333.76094090422300aLiving with the Land :bRural and Agricultural Actors in Twentieth-Century Europe – A Handbook /ced. by Liesbeth van de Grift, Dietmar Müller, Corinna R. Unger. 1aMünchen ;aWien : bDe Gruyter Oldenbourg, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (VIII, 363 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aContemporary European History ,x2627-0366 ;v300tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tOn the “Contemporary European History” Handbook Series -- t1 Living with the Land: Introduction -- tI Working the Land -- t2 Opening Up the Land: Infrastructures in Rural Europe -- t3 Reclaiming the Land: The Drainage Paradigm and the Making of Twentieth-Century Rural Europe -- t4 Developing Rural Regions: Europe in the World -- tII Managing Land and Labor -- t5 Mediating Modernity: The Social History of Rural Domestic Education in Northwestern Europe -- t6 Pooling Resources in the European Countryside: Cooperative Models, Rural Capitalism, and Beyond -- t7 Farming under Occupation: Rural Actors and the Social Dynamics of Occupation during World War II -- t8 Transforming Agriculture and Rurality: The Common Agricultural Policy, Actors, National Adaptation and Responses to Policy Challenges -- tIII Knowing the Land -- t9 Registering Land and Forests: European Institutions and Practices of Landownership -- t10 Experimenting with Scientific Management: New Approaches to Agricultural Labor in the Twentieth Century -- t11 Developing Agriculture, Modernizing Rural Society: Transnational Dimensions of Agricultural Expertise -- tIV Organizing Life on the Land -- t12 Representing Peasants and Farmers: Parties, Movements, and Leaders Across Europe -- t13 Governing the Village: Rural Mayors and the Transformations of Self-Government in Europe -- t14 Managing Culture in the European Countryside: The Modern Roots of Rural Traditions -- t15 Challenging Socialist Village Structures: Youth in Rural Regions since 1945 -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFor a long time agriculture and rural life were dismissed by many contemporaries as irrelevant or old-fashioned. Contrasted with cities as centers of intellectual debate and political decision-making, the countryside seemed to be becoming increasingly irrelevant. Today, politicians in many European countries are starting to understand that the neglect of the countryside has created grave problems. Similarly, historians are remembering that European history in the twentieth century was strongly influenced by problems connected to the production of food, access to natural resources, land rights, and the political representation and activism of rural populations. Hence, the handbook offers an overview of historical knowledge on a variety of topics related to the land. It does so through a distinctly activity-centric and genuinely European perspective. Rather than comparing different national approaches to living with the land, the different chapters focus on particular activities – from measuring to settling the land, from producing and selling food to improving agronomic knowledge, from organizing rural life to challenging political structures in the countryside. Furthermore, the handbook overcomes the traditional division between East and West, North and South, by embracing a transregional approach that allows readers to gain an understanding of similarities and differences across national and ideological borders in twentieth-century Europe.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aAgriculturezEuropexHistoryy20th century. 0aLand usezEuropexHistoryy20th century. 4aBewirtschaftung. 4aLandwirtschaft. 4aRepräsentation. 4anatürliche Ressourcen.  aagriculture.  amanagement.  anatural resources.  arepresentation.1 aBerry, Gustav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBruisch, Katja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForclaz, Amalia Ribi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeering, Corinne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGermond, Carine S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeronymaki, Kalliopi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrift, Liesbeth van de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartmann, Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHüchtker, Dietlind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamenov, Nikolay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLagendijk, Vincent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLučić, Iva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeurs, Wim van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Dietmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Dietmar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchlimm, Anette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaratko, Carolyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTönsmeyer, Tatjana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUnger, Corinna R., econtribut